cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.SY, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on developing a practical geo-distributed data analytics system that efficiently utilizes resources across data centers. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the challenges of running a wide range of data analytics jobs without requiring any changes. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is another possible category as the paper deals with managing and processing large amounts of data across multiple data centers. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper presents a new system, HOUTU, that is composed of multiple autonomous systems. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the challenges of WAN bandwidth limits and regulatory constraints in geo-distributed data analytics.
